# MPI_CODES

This repository contains a collection of **Message Passing Interface (MPI)** programs demonstrating various parallel computing paradigms, including **blocking**, **non-blocking**, and **collective communication**.

## Features

- **Blocking Communication**: Synchronous send/receive operations.
- **Non-Blocking Communication**: Asynchronous operations enabling computation and communication overlap.
- **Collective Communication**: Operations like broadcast and gather for multi-process data exchange.


## Prerequisites

- **MPI Library**: [Open MPI](https://www.open-mpi.org/) or [MPICH](https://www.mpich.org/)
- **C Compiler**: e.g., `gcc`

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Zain4391/MPI_CODES.git
   cd MPI_CODES
2. mpicc -o output_file path/to/example.c
3. mpiexec -n 4 ./output_file
